atDirectives.description:
Use the `@import` directive to import CSS files. Tailwind CSS v4 uses this to import the framework:
```css
@import "tailwindcss";
```

Use the `@theme` directive to define custom design tokens (colors, spacing, shadows, etc.) in your CSS. This replaces the JavaScript config in v4:
```css
@theme {
  --color-primary: #09c;
  --shadow-hero: 0 4px 6px -1px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.1);
}
```

Use the `@layer` directive to organize your custom CSS into Tailwind's layer system:
```css
@layer components {
  .btn {
    @apply px-4 py-2 rounded;
  }
}
```

Use the `@utility` directive to create custom utility classes in Tailwind CSS v4:
```css
@utility text-balance {
  text-wrap: balance;
}
```
